OOP-> Object Oriented Programming

Features of OOP

1)Object:Any Entity which has own state and behaviour that is called an object

2)Class:collection of objects that is called class

3)Abstraction:Hiding internal details and showing functionalities that is called abstraction

4)Encapsulation:Wrapping up of data or binding of data that is called encapsulation

5)Inheritance:When one object acquire all the properties and behaviour of parent class that is called an inheritance

6)Polymorphism:Many ways to perform anything that is called polymorphism


